g.title: Sheet.405
g.desc: Foriegn packages are exclusively copied-to/contained within a...
g.text: Foriegn packages are exclusively copied-to/contained within a subdir directory of the Outcast Repo. · Because the Outcast directory structure differs from the FO’s source repo, the FO unit tests may not be directly buildable

g.title: Sheet.421
g.desc: Overlay packages have their primary source tree overlayed on ...
g.text: Overlay packages have their primary source tree overlayed on top of the Outcast repo’s primary packages source tree when the OV package is copied into the Outcast repo.· Provides the most scalability because:· Only the Source’s primary package is copied in. This prevents multiple instances of the same package being adopted when there are transitive dependencies.· There is a single/common directory structure for build scripts/makefiles.· The OV package’s unit test are buildable/executable within the Outcast repo without modifications.
